---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CaseConverter from '../../components/CaseConverter.jsx';
import RelatedTools from '../../components/RelatedTools.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Case Converter Free – UPPER, lower, Title, camelCase"
  description="Convert text to UPPERCASE, lowercase, Title Case, Sentence case, camelCase, snake_case and kebab-case instantly. Free online case converter, no login required."
>
  <div class="tool-page">
    <div class="tool-header">
      <a href="/categories/text-tools/" class="back-link">← Text Tools</a>
      <h1 class="tool-title">Text Case Converter</h1>
      <p class="tool-subtitle">Convert any text to uppercase, lowercase, title case, camelCase, snake_case, kebab-case and more in one click.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-horizontal">
      <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" data-ad-slot="1234567890" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
      <script is:inline>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
    </div>

    <CaseConverter client:load />

    <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-horizontal" style="margin-top: 32px;">
      <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" data-ad-slot="0987654321" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
      <script is:inline>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
    </div>

    <section class="seo-content">
      <h2>What cases are supported?</h2>
      <p>UPPERCASE (every letter capitalized), lowercase (every letter small), Title Case (first letter of each word capitalized), Sentence case (only the first word capitalized), camelCase (used in JavaScript and Java variable names), snake_case (used in Python and database column names) and kebab-case (used in CSS class names and URL slugs).</p>

      <h2>When would I need a case converter?</h2>
      <p>Developers use it to convert variable names or API keys between naming conventions — for example, renaming a database column from snake_case to camelCase for a JavaScript API response. Writers use it to quickly fix accidentally typed text. Designers use it to test how headings look in Title Case vs Sentence case. Marketers use it to ensure consistent brand name capitalization across documents.</p>

      <h2>What is camelCase?</h2>
      <p>camelCase joins words together with no spaces, capitalizing the first letter of each word except the first (e.g. "myVariableName"). It is named for the humps that the capital letters resemble. It is the standard naming convention for variables and functions in JavaScript, Java, Swift and many other languages. PascalCase is the same but with the first letter also capitalized.</p>

      <h2>What is snake_case?</h2>
      <p>snake_case uses underscores to separate words, with all letters lowercase (e.g. "my_variable_name"). It is the standard in Python, Ruby, and SQL database column names. It is easier to read than camelCase for longer identifiers and is preferred by many style guides for constants when written in SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE.</p>

      <h2>Is my text stored?</h2>
      <p>No. All conversion happens entirely in your browser. Your text is never sent to any server or stored anywhere.</p>
    </section>

    <RelatedTools slugs={["word-count", "text-diff", "lorem-ipsum"]} />
  </div>
</Layout>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "Text Case Converter",
  "url": "https://www.pixmidas.com/tools/case-converter/",
  "applicationCategory": "UtilitiesApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Any",
  "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript",
  "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
  "description": "Convert text to uppercase, lowercase, title case, camelCase, snake_case and kebab-case instantly. Free, no login."
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What text cases does the converter support?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "UPPERCASE, lowercase, Title Case, Sentence case, camelCase, snake_case, and kebab-case. Each is applied instantly with one click." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is camelCase and when do developers use it?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "camelCase joins words with no spaces, capitalizing the first letter of each word except the first (e.g. myVariableName). It is the standard naming convention for variables and functions in JavaScript, Java, Swift and many other languages." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is snake_case used for?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "snake_case uses underscores to separate words with all letters lowercase (e.g. my_variable_name). It is the standard in Python, Ruby, and SQL database column names." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is my text stored when using the case converter?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. All conversion happens entirely in your browser. Your text is never sent to any server or stored anywhere." }
    }
  ]
}
</script>
